HEADWORD: Johnsonese
<hw>John`son*ese"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The literary
style of <person>Dr. Samuel <etsep>Johnson</etsep></person>, or one
formed in imitation of it; an inflated, stilted, or pompous style,
affecting classical words.</def> <rj><au>E. Everett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

